My question is about the line "packets.add(s.toPacket());". Why are outgoing packages queued? Why simply not use 
[code]
p.getSession().write(packet);
[/code]

The only explanation I see is that players will receive updates together, with a fixed delay (whenever the update loop runs), but I don't really see a reason for this.
